<br>
- You have to attend a sky raid and be there for the entire raid.  One of the reasons I suggested this strategy is that I will not likely attend a full sky raid ever again.  I don't have the fiance faction to spend 4 days straight (plus time for additional clearings)<br>
- Everytime you want to refresh your corpse you burn a sky stone.  Not a big deal.  But it is a recurring cost every week.<br>
- You don't know if someone else recently appeared and cleared the 7th island without burning a coffin (if you hadn't summoned it recently) and a skystone.  You could bring along a tracker friend probably to check.<br>
- Although I'm not entirely sure, why on the last sky raid I went on, when our wizard jumped off one of the islands naked (woohoo), when she came back and looted her corpse her keys were gone.  That could have been caused by her casting the sky port to get back up instead of jumping off, I don't know.<br>
- You burn an essense emerald everytime you restart a raid.  Again, not a big deal since you can get one before hand.<br>
- Your big risk is forgetting your corpse and it rots.  You need to do a while raid again to reestablish this strategy.<br>
<br>
Of course there are drawbacks to my strategy:<br>
- You burn two alts.  46 necro and 46 pally/cleric aren't trivial.  This is huge (as I'm finding)<br>
- You depend on finding a sky raid that reaches the 7th isle.  This could take a while.<br>
- The upfront costs are much higher, although the long term costs are non existant, and restart costs are also non-existant (beyond the normal summoning you don't need anything to restart the chain)<br>
- Your biggest risk is not rezzing the duel corpse in time.<br>
<br>
There are always multiple approaches to things in the game.  I'm glad we are talking about it.  There are non-brute force ways to do our epics.  MQ and camped alts (or necro corpses with keys) are viable tools for doing our epic.<br>
<br>
